-- China March fiscal revenues up 5.2 pct yr/yr
-- 
-- Thu Apr 17, 2014 04:24AM EDT
-- None



BEIJING, April 17 (Reuters) - China's fiscal revenues in March rose 5.2 percent from a year earlier to 1.01 trillion yuan ($162.3 billion), the Ministry of Finance said on Thursday, slowing from a rise of 11.1 percent in the first two months of this year.

Fiscal revenues in the first quarter rose 9.3 percent from the same period last year to 3.5 trillion yuan, the ministry said in a statement on its website, www.mof.gov.cn